-- MTN Group Appoints Mroué as Chief Executive of Ugandan Operation
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2012-06-18T08:59:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-18/mtn-group-appoints-mrou-as-chief-executive-of-ugandan-operation.html
MTN Group Ltd., Africa’s biggest
mobile-phone company, named Mazen Mroué as chief executive
officer of its Ugandan unit.  Mroué, formerly chief information officer for MTN Ghana
Ltd., replaces Themba Khumalo, who was named as the group’s
operations executive for 13 countries including Afghanistan,
Yemen, Botswana, Zambia, Swaziland and Sudan, MTN Uganda said
today by e-mail from Kampala, the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
